| The Belgian Army consisted of 22 divisions, the French provided 104, the British provided 10, and the Dutch 8 divisions. {{harvnb|Holmes|2001|p=324}}.
}}
{{efn
| name = Netherlands
|Contributed lightly armed infantry units retreating from Dutch territory. Also committed the Dutch Air Force on few, ineffective and costly missions. {{harvnb|Gunsburg|1992|p=216}}.
}}
{{efn
| name = Guns
| The Belgian Army had 1,338 guns, the French 10,700, the British 1,280, and the Dutch 656. {{harvnb|Holmes|2001|p=324}}.
}}
{{efn
| name = tanks
| The Belgian Army had 10 tanks, the French 3,063, the British 310 and the Dutch 1 tank. {{harvnb|Holmes|2001|p=324}}.
}}
{{efn
| name = Aircraft
| The Belgian Air Force consisted of 250 aircraft, the French Air Force 1,368, the British Royal Air Force provided 456 aircraft and the Dutch Air Force 175. {{harvnb|Holmes|2001|p=324}}.
}}
{{efn
| name = Men lost
| The Belgian Army sustained 6,093 men killed, 15,850 men wounded in action, more than 500 men missing and 200,000 men captured, of which 2,000 died in captivity. {{harvnb|Keegan|2005|p=96}}; {{harvnb|Ellis|1993|p=255}}. French and British losses on Belgian territory are unknown. {{harvnb|Keegan|2005|p=96}}.
}}
{{efn
| name = Aircraft lost
| The Belgian Air Force lost 83 planes on the ground on 10 May, 25 lost in aerial combat between 10–15 May, and four lost in the air between 16–28 May. {{harvnb|Hooton|2007|pp=49, 52, 53}}.  French and British losses are not certain, however the French Air Force lost 264 aircraft between 12–25 May and 50 for 26 May – 1 June while the British Royal Air Force lost 344 and 138 aircraft in these respective periods. {{harvnb|Hooton|2007|p=57}}.
}}
{{efn
| name = German casualties
| German air units doubled up and flew missions over the Netherlands and Belgium. Case specific loss totals for Belgium only cannot be certain. Total German losses in the air numbered 469 in 12–25 May, and 126 for 26 May – 1 June, but at least 43 paratroopers were killed and a further 100 wounded. {{harvnb|Hooton|2007|p=57}};   {{harvnb|Dunstan|2005|p=57}}.
}}
